snippet.title: Star Wars: Rogue Squadron 3D PC Gameplay
snippet.description:
A quick look-see at a classic, or a test video for a future LP hmmmm? :D

Getting this game to install on win7 64 bit was a task and a half. The installer on the disc won't even run, joystick support barely functions, a glide wrapper is pretty much required, and it took an upgrade from a Radeon HD 6850 to a GTX 660 just to get it to record on OBS without hitching. A freaking GTX 660 just for a 15 year old game! (not really but it works)
